basketball semifinal.
   Simon has made a bet with Sen. Carl Levin of Michigan, and if
Illinois loses, Simon will wear a clip-on bow tie dotted with
Michigan's ``M'' logo.
   If Illinois wins the game, Levin will wear an Illini straight
tie.
   To make things even more interesting, the senators also have
added soda to the stakes, throwing in two cases of Michigan
Vernor's ginger ale and two cases of Illinois-bottled Orange Crush.
   ``I've never worn a clip on, and I'm confident I never will have
to wear a clip on,'' Simon said.
   Retorted Levin: ``Senator Simon will make history in wearing a
Michigan clip-on bow tie after the `orange crush' is made into
`blue' slush Saturday night.''
