<HEAD>Stagehand Killed In Accident At Royal Opera House</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A cart carrying heavy scenery fell on a stagehand
after a rehearsal at London's Royal Opera House, fatally injuring
the man, management said.
   The wagon full of scenery was being moved across the stage
Friday when it toppled over onto 31-year-old stage technician Greg
Ballamy, said Ewen Balfour, opera house spokesman. He said Ballamy
died soon afterward in University College Hospital.
   That evening's performance of Giuseppe Verdi's ``Don Carlo'' was
canceled in sympathy for the man's family.
   Balfour said it was the first fatality since the current opera
house was completed in 1858. A management statement said there
would be an inquiry into the accident.
