<HEAD>Congressman Dies Of Heart Attack</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tito Dupaya, a member of the
Philippine House of Representatives and ally of President Corazon
Aquino, died today of heart attack in his northern home province of
Cagayan, authorities said. He was 67.
   Dupaya was en route to the Cagayan airport to meet Justice
Secretary Sedfey Ordonez when he complained of chest pains, said
Thelma Maceda, House spokesperson.
   He was rushed to the Cagayan hospital where he died of heart
attack at 8:30 a.m., Maceda added. Cagayan is about 210 miles
northeast of Manila.
   Dupaya is a member of the Struggle of the Democratic Filipino
party, the main political group supporting President Aquino.
   He served for two terms under former President Ferdinand Marcos'
administration. Marcos fled to Hawaii where he is in exile in 1986.
   Dupaya is survived by his wife Teresa, a former Cagayan
governor, and two sons and three daughters.
