<SECOND>PM-BRF--Television Arrest,0167</SECOND>
<HEAD>TV Feature Leads To Fugitive's Arrest</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BLUEFIELD, W.Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man wanted for questioning in the
sexual assault of his 5-year-old niece was arrested in Florida
after the victim's mother recognized him in a news story about a
traveling carnival.
   John Lloyd Kast, 59, of Ronceverte left town after the alleged
assault and joined a carnival that was working in southern Florida,
police said.
   Miami television station WTVJ had done a feature story on the
carnival that aired on NBC's affiliate news feed this week. WVVA-TV
in Bluefield aired the story on Tuesday's 11 p.m. newscast.
   Kast was pictured for three seconds during the 1{-minute
feature, neighbors recognized him and told the girl's mother. She
reviewed videotapes of the newscast at the station the next day.
   ``That's him. That's him,'' she said.
   WVVA contacted the Greenbrier County sheriff's office, which
contacted Miami police.
   Kast was arrested Friday and an extradition hearing was
scheduled for Monday.
