<HEAD>Three East Germans Ram Border Barriers But Escape Attempt Fails</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERLIN (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three East Germans trying to escape to the West
crashed a car through a border barrier but were captured by guards,
police said today.
   Witnesses heard several gunshots during the incident Friday
night at the Drewitz control point between East Germany and West
Berlin, a West Berlin police spokesman said.
   ``The car rammed through a border barrier and then smashed
against another. Border guards then took the three men away,'' said
the spokesman, who spoke on condition of anonymity.
   East Germany's state-run news agency, ADN, also reported the
incident but did not mention shooting or characterize it as an
escape attempt.
   According to ADN, three ``traffic rowdies'' were arrested for
``excessive speed'' and ``security installations'' were damaged.
   The Drewitz control point is just east of Potsdam, East Germany,
and on the southwestern periphery of West Berlin.
