<HEAD>Entertainer Gene Kelly Recuperating Well From Pneumonia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gene Kelly, the quintessential song-and-dance
man, was in fair condition Saturday and recuperating quickly at a
hospital after he cancelled a weekend performance because of
pneumonia.
   ``He's walking around and will probably be released Monday,''
said Cedars-Sinai hospital spokesman Ron Wise.
   Kelly, 76, entered the hospital and was admitted under a
pseudonym Wednesday. ``He came in quietly,'' Wise said. ``His
physicians didn't want him to be bothered by phone calls or
visitors.''
   The illness forced the actor-dancer to cancel a performance of
his one-man show ``Evening with Gene Kelly'' at the La Mirada Civic
Center Friday night.
   Theater spokeswoman Beverly Hamlin said the performance was not
rescheduled and refunds would be given to 1,300 fans. Kelly has
appeared in such films as ``Hello Dolly,'' ``American in Paris,''
and ``Anchors Aweigh.''
